{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17508536","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17508536"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T12:06:21+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T12:06:21+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2774"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"2774","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/2774"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.11,0.08,0.09,0.64,0.09]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"2774"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"106623"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"2774","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/2774"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2774"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"89100"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"19"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"759"},{"type":"tags","id":"1179"},{"type":"tags","id":"4964"},{"type":"tags","id":"4974"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"9294"},{"type":"tags","id":"9598"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11633"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"},{"type":"tags","id":"12920"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"3704"},{"type":"contributions","id":"4119"},{"type":"contributions","id":"4128"},{"type":"contributions","id":"39395"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44528"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"106623","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/106623"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 77-year-old woman presents to the General Practice clinic with a two-month history of a painless swelling in her right groin (Image). This is more noticeable when she stands. Her medical history includes hypertension, atrial fibrillation and excision of a melanoma from her right leg two years ago. Her medications include perindopril and warfarin. Recently she had a course of antibiotics for a chest infection. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, she appears well with vital signs within normal limits. The swelling is soft, non-reducible and there is no cough impulse. The swelling lies below the inguinal ligament. The rest of the physical examination is normal.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Metastatic lymph node deposits","Rectus sheath haematoma","Lipoma","Femoral hernia","Hydrocele of the canal of Nuck"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe most likely cause of this swelling in the right groin is a hernia. \u003Cstrong\u003EFemoral hernias\u003C/strong\u003E are more common in women and they are almost always irreducible. They are also more common than inguinal hernias over the age of 70. However, in terms of overall frequency of groin hernias in women, the inguinal hernia is more usual. Whilst most inguinal hernias will usually have a cough impulse, this is not the case with a femoral hernia, where a cough impulse is often absent. This is because the neck of the canal is narrow and the contents of the sac often immobile.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA \u003Cstrong\u003Elipoma\u003C/strong\u003E would demonstrate a slipping sign on examination. They are also commonly present for many years and may change with weight. Lipomas tend to occur on the trunk and the groin would be a less common site to find them.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA \u003Cstrong\u003Erectus sheath haematoma\u003C/strong\u003E would be more towards the midline and as most of these bleeds occur posterior to the rectus abdominis muscle, any associated swelling would not be so pronounced and well circumscribed as that visible in this patient. However, it is very reasonable to consider such a diagnosis in a patient who may be over-anticoagulated - typically someone on warfarin who is put on antibiotics, with a subsequent increase in the INR and risk of spontaneous bleeding.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMetastatic lymph node deposits\u003C/strong\u003E from the previously treated melanoma must be considered. However, in terms of frequency, this swelling is more likely to be a hernia given its location and characteristics.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA \u003Cstrong\u003Ehydrocele of the canal of Nuck\u003C/strong\u003E is an uncommon congenital defect and tends to be found in children or young women. It is the result of a failure of complete obliteration of the canal of Nuck, with the formation of an isolated collection of fluid in the inguinal canal.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Most groin swellings are either an inguinal or femoral hernia."],"references":["Fitzgibbons RJ, Armour Forse R. Groin Hernias in Adults. N Engl J Med 2015; 372:756-63."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"89100"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2774"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"17772"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"17772","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/17772"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/9bc8b0e7-dce6-4d0e-b9fa-b3be271f3197.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/9bc8b0e7-dce6-4d0e-b9fa-b3be271f3197.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":587,"height":440}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"89100","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/89100"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-06-20T22:51:30+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-06-20T22:51:31+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"